# Conclusions
There was no real impact in using different covariance structures on the magnitude of parameter estimates, LRT and marginal BLUPS.
Among the 10 individuals with the highest marginal BLUP values, all models selected the same set of individuals, with the exception of the model fitted using the rr+diag variance–covariance structure, which differed by only one individual relative to the others.
